title: For Sale:  -- 9 MM Model 92 Taurus (Beretta Mfg License)
postcontent:
This 9 MM caliber Taurus Model 92 is made on the license of the famous Beretta 92 series. The open top slide virtually eliminates jamming and stove piping and allows the user to load and chamber one cartridge at a time should the magazine be lost or damaged.
 
FEATURES: Safeties:  ambidextrous safety on both sides of frame. 
Loaded chamber indicator along side barrel.
Single and double action. Single action has a nice clean break -- it’s short, light (about five pounds) and crisp!
Real hammer fired – this is the classic hammer you can pull back with your thumb and actually feel and see firing the gun, a feature favored by many shooters as a more authentic shooting experience.
Breech-locking mechanism uses a Walther-style tilting locking block.
Construction: Steel barrel and slide.  Sturdy metal alloy frame.
5 inch barrel and military/ergonomic frame achieves legendary pointability and accuracy.
Recoil is very manageable. Strong, planted grip with checkered wood grips means that the recoil does not snap or kick  --  more of a "push" and really cushions the recoil.  Even shooters accustomed to a lighter round will be able to handle it very easily.
Full Pachmayer Signature Grips have full checkering all around (360 degrees) for a secure grip.
Double stack, high capacity magazine.
Field stripping is a snap, using Beretta’s sure-footed, quick lever takedown that easily removes the slide from the frame. From there, the recoil spring, guide tube and barrel are easily removed.
Unbeatable Taurus lifetime warranty (transferrable to all subsequent owners).
** The features, fit and finish of its more expensive cousins that it easily rivals. Note the absence of machine marks, a characteristic of higher end firearms.
 
Carry options: Drop the hammer all the way down and carry it chambered, hammer down, off safe for a first double action shot.  You can also keep the safety on, then thumb it off with and have a first double action shot.  If you are a 1911 fan, then you can also carry cocked and locked which is the hammer cocked, safety on with a first shot being single action.
Includes high capacity magazine.

postcontent: Heckler & Koch HK VP9sk LE brand new unfiredThis is the new May 2017 released 9mm rare Law Enforcement (LE) subcompact from HK.  The "LE" is the Mod 2 version that comes with factory tritium night sights (versus standard luminescent requiring light) and a third magazine with the finger extension.This new never fired hk vp9sk LE comes with tthe factory tritium dot night sights, 3-10 round mags, speed loader, grip adapters, box, manuals, and lock.The VP Series is Heckler & Koch's first striker-fired HK since the P7 series pistols introduced in the 1980s. It is well-suited for civilian sport shooting, security, military, and law enforcement use. The VP Series integrates a striker firing system with an enhanced, HK "light pull" trigger. HK's cold hammer-forged barrel made from cannon grade steel ensures long service life, as does the polygonal bore profile which also provides a slight increase in muzzle velocity. All controls are completely ambidextrous. Slide releases are present on both sides of the frame, and the paddle-style magazine release can be easily activated by left- or right-handed shooters. A unique VP feature is HK's patented rear-mounted charging supports on each side of the slide provide better gripping leverage for racking the slide rearward. postcontent: Selling my custom tactical Remington 870. Lots of tactical mods done on this. Shoots both 2 3/4 and 3" inch shells. XS tritium Big Dot rifle sights were installed as well. Gun comes with the following upgrades: -PRI Picatinny rail installed on receiver -MagPul 870 forend and MLOK rail -Speedfeed stock -GG&G Stainless Magazine Hi-Viz Follower -Daniel Defense Burnsend Stock Sling Loop -Cerakoted Graphite Black/Bolt is Micro Slicked -XS Tritium Big Dot Rifle sights installed. Tritium still works. -Jumbo head safety (not installed) This gun shoots great and recoil is very manageable with both the vented choke system and excellent Speedfeed stock.
